  section(data-animation="tennis-racket")
    .flex-slide
      h2 Finding 2D eigenfunctions
      div(style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr")
        p Horizontal:
          | $$ f(x, y_j) = \sum_{k=0}^\infty c_k^{(y_j)} \beta_k^{(y_j)}(x) $$
        p Vertical:
          | $$ f(x_i, y) = \sum_{k=0}^\infty c_k^{(x_i)} \beta_k^{(x_i)}(y) $$
      div(style="margin-top: -30px")
        | $$ -\frac{\text{d}^2\,\beta_k^{(y_j)}}{\text{d}x^2} + \frac{V(x, y_j)}{2} \beta_k^{(y_j)} = \lambda_k^{(y_j)} \beta_k $$
      .fragment(data-animation="beta-matrices")
        p If these sums are finite, this yields a matrix-problem:
          | $$ \mathbf{B_x} \mathbf{\Lambda_x}\mathbf{c_x} + \mathbf{B_y} \mathbf{\Lambda_y}\mathbf{c_y} = E \mathbf{B_x} \mathbf{c_x} = E \mathbf{B_y} \mathbf{c_y}\text{.} $$

